4:
I told you not to touch anything...
Adjudicus.
6:
My apologies, Uncle—I mean, Lord
Oghir!
9:
All you'll find here is the books from
Belsidia, as you can already tell
from your rummaging, I'm sure.
14: Enough. Call me what you will.
16:
Then... Uncle, I actually came looking
for you. I wanted to continue our
discussion from the other day.
19:
...Didn't your father just scold you for
wasting your time conversing with
me?
21:
Father is easily placated. It's nothing
a good spar with him shouldn't fix.
22:
Besides, he should be busy planning
the next military campaign. They're
going to be searching for the Lord's
Vessel.
24:
Do you think... Father and
Grandfather intend to birth a new
Lord of Shadow?
28:
To do so would thrust
Pandemonium into war... Your
grandfather would doubtless lose
his position—if not his life.
30: Then why bother with this campaign?
33:
To discourage any potential
rebellion, I imagine.
35:
They'll be able to increase the
number of daemons in the army
under the pretense of being chosen
by the vessel...
36:
Not that anyone will believe that for
a moment, of course. But your
grandfather will relish their envy all
the same.
38:
...Perhaps I shouldn't stand idly by
while he puts his plans in motion.
40:
Pay my muttering no heed.
In any case, I assume you wish to
continue the lecture from the other
day.
42:
Yes—about the history of currency
from other worlds.
45:
Ah, I believe we left off with how
specific precious metals actually
determined the value of money. But
the most fascinating part is—
54:
Y-you cannot pass! The ritual is well
underway—
60:
There must be some sort of mistake!
Uncle would never plot a rebellion!
67:
Be a good boy and stay out of this,
Adjudicus. I will avenge your father's
death now...
74:
Enough lies. Do not disgrace yourself
any further with more treachery.
75:
I knew you were always envious of
your brother... But to murder him
over it?
78:
He was the epitome of brilliance and
beauty. He should have been the
one to end it all.
79: He WOULD have been the one...
81:
And yet why is it that you live while
he does not?
85:
We are similar, Oghir. We burn with
hatred for the fools of the world...
and smolder with envy for those
possessed of radiance and beauty.
87:
Hahaha... You know I speak true. 
You and I are the same!
88:
Perhaps there is no other more fit to
be Lord of Shadow than you...
100:
I can hear them... I can hear the
voices... of all those wretched and
weak like us.
106: Let us dream together... as one.
110:
The Lord of Shadow was born that
day.
111:
Swallowed by misery and hatred, 
he quietly began his conquest.
112:
He crushed the Champion... and
betrayed the fiends.
117:
Thanks for agreeing to this, but... are
you sure you want to go through
with it?
120:
If I am to face my uncle—the Lord of
Shadow... I require the same power.
124:
Do it. Bestow upon me that cursed
power.
128:
O darkness that dwells within all
creation, ever in eternal
lamentation... Rise, and be given
form.
144:
So this... is the true form... of the
curse!
146:
You were the voices... my uncle
heard!
155:
You restrained the curse through
willpower alone...
156:
You might actually be able to
command it... Unlike Oghir, who
could not.
159:
Still, I hope there is a future where
the both of you can walk the same
path...
164:
I will take this curse... and its power...
and use it to the bitter end!
168:
So come, daemons and all! I am
ready!
174:
I will show you what a true Lord
should be.
